Reykjavík City then launched the zoning process and completed it with an announcement in Stjórnartíðindum in July last year.
That scheme was also challenged and the committee ruled it invalid in March 2020.
At this point, nearly three years had passed since the original application for a building permit and the owners of the property were still at the starting line.
